   <A HREF="https://theintercept.com/2020/03/05/iran-coronavirus-medicine-sanctions/" TARGET="news"><img src="http://www.payvand.com/news/20/mar/UANI-Targets-Medicine-Sales-to-Iran-i.jpg" hspace="4" align="right" width="200"></a>
   <div class="newssum">DESPITE A MASSIVE coronavirus-related public health crisis, an anti-Iran pressure group with close ties to the Trump administration is urging major pharmaceutical companies to &#34;end their Iran business,&#34; focusing on companies with special licenses - most often under a broadly defined &#34;humanitarian exemption&#34; - to conduct trade with Iran. -Eli Clifton, Intercept 03/6/20</div>
